# JobJitsu — Generate Git commit message

When Cursor auto-generates a Git commit message for this repository (Source Control sparkle / AI Commit), follow these rules exactly.

## Required format

```
<type>(optional-scope): <lowercase imperative subject>

- Short bullet about why or what changed
- Another bullet if needed
```

Output **only** that message. No markdown fences. No preamble. No “This commit…”.

## Types (header must start with one)

`feat` | `fix` | `chore` | `docs` | `refactor` | `perf` | `test` | `build` | `ci` | `style` | `revert`

## Hard rules (Commitlint will reject otherwise)

- Header: `type` then optional `(kebab-scope)` then `: ` then subject
- Subject: lowercase, imperative (“add”, “fix”, “drive”), no trailing period, max 100 chars
- Body: one blank line after header; only `- ` bullets; each line max 100 chars
- Scope optional, kebab-case: `app`, `events`, `core`, `ai`, `tooling`, `brand`, `extension-sdk`

## Copy this style (recent good commits)

```
feat(app): drive host through an event cascade

- Add App.Started, Plugin.Loaded, Resume.Generated, and Email.Synced
- Own fake AI in the host; fence shell UI from importing @jobjitsu/ai
```

```
chore(tooling): commit after each completed prompt

- Add cursor rule to land Conventional Commits when a slice finishes
```

## Never generate (wrong)

```
Add initial project structure and configuration files
This commit establishes the foundational structure...
```

```
Update README with new architecture details.
```

```
Implement ESLint and Prettier configurations, add commitlint...
```

No type prefix, essay paragraphs, Title Case subjects, or trailing periods on the subject.
